8.19.22  6:38 am   What's it called when a song just suspends or pause sort of speak with, like a pad sound. No drum sound. No established tempo. What is called when a song doesn't have a tempo and no drums and it's just free flowing based on how the singer or musician wants to play the song?

     it might be called "free time", or, the more traditional italian marking is 'rubato' which means there is no time or tempo.

      Is it similar to a vamp.

     no, kind of the opposite. a vamp is in time (has a beat / tempo)

      What is a vamp?

      that's like when you keep repeating a few bars of a groove, just chillin there letting the beat go around
